<div class="pa4 black-80 avenir mt5">
  <div class="measure-wide center lh-copy">
    <h1 class="f1 fw3">Calculating AMT</h1>
    <p class="f4">
      We first start with your adjusted gross income. For the purposes of this back-of-the-envelope calculation, we use your annual gross salary. Note that there are many other adjustments that influence this number.
    </p>
    <p class="f4">
      Then, we add adjustments to get to the alternative minimum taxable income (“AMTI”). For this site, we only consider the spread on an ISO exercise. However, there are many other types of deductions subject to AMT.
    </p>
    <p class="f4">
      From AMTI, we less the AMT exemptions to get to the AMT base. The actual exemption amount depends on your filing status. Learn more about calculating AMT exemptions. Here is the table for determining the exemption amounts for 2016.
    </p>
    <p class="f4">
      We calculate the tentative minimum tax by applying the AMT rate (either 26% or 28%, depending on the amount) to the AMT base.
    </p>
    <p class="f4">
      Finally, we compare the tentative minimum tax to your ordinary income tax. Your payable tax will be the greater of either the tentative minimum tax or the ordinary income tax.
    </p>
